BotResponse: Phishing is a type of cyber attack where attackers attempt to trick individuals into providing sensitive information such as usernames, passwords, and credit card details by posing as a trustworthy entity in an electronic communication. To protect yourself from phishing attacks, be cautious of unsolicited emails or messages requesting personal information, verify the legitimacy of the sender before clicking on any links or attachments, and use security software to help detect and prevent phishing attempts.
